column1: #Text=The Golden State Warriors defeated the Utah Jazz , 104 - 74 , at Oracle Arena on Saturday .
#Text=Golden State was expected to win this game easily , but it took a monster second half to escape with a win .

column6: The Warriors didnâ€™t need, or have, and monster 2nd half to win this game

column1: #Text=In fact , the Warriors led for the entirety of the second half , as they held a double - digit lead for the final 30 - plus minutes .
#Text=Defense was key for Golden State , as they held the Jazz to 36 percent from the field and 30 percent from three - point range .
#Text=Rebounding was a huge factor for the Warriors , as they won that battle , 50 - 44 .
#Text=Kevin Durant was the player of the game , as he tallied 22 points and five rebounds on 8 - of - 14 shooting .
#Text=Draymond Green finished second on the team with 15 points , 11 rebounds and four assists .
#Text=Rudy Gobert recorded a double - double , totaling 11 points and 17 rebounds .
#Text=Klay Thompson led the team in scoring , as he dropped 17 points on 8 - of - 13 shooting .

column6: Thompson did not lead the Warriors in scoring

column1: #Text=Draymond Green recorded a double - double , totaling 15 points , 11 rebounds , four assists and five steals .
#Text=Joe Johnson was the only other starter in double figures , as he accrued 14 points and two rebounds .
#Text=Gordon Hayward was the player of the game , as he accumulated 25 points , three rebounds and four assists .
#Text=Rudy Gobert was the only other Jazz player in double figures , as he totaled 11 points and 17 rebounds .
